MainApp

CheatClient is a custom client application developed as a personal project to explore client-side modification, networking interaction, and software architecture concepts.

📌 Description

MainApp is designed as a modular client that demonstrates how custom features and extended functionality can be integrated into an existing environment.
The project focuses on performance, flexibility, and clean code structure.

⚙️ Features

Modular architecture

Custom client-side functionality

Configuration system

Optimized performance handling

User-friendly interface

Expandable feature system

🛠️ Technologies Used

C#

.NET

Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)

Client-side architecture principles

🎯 Purpose

This project was created for:

learning purposes

improving programming skills

understanding client modification logic

experimenting with software design patterns

🚀 Installation

Clone the repository:

git clone https://github.com/sh1ne01/MainApp.git

Open the solution in Visual Studio.

Build the project.

Run the client.

